<h1 id="cc-title" class="text-center">Monk</h1>

<h2 id="cc-subtitle" class="text-center mb-5">Way of the Destruction Style</h2>

<p id="subclass-overview-text" class="text-left mx-5 mb-5 p-2 rounded">
    <i>You are trained in the Destruction Style, a martial arts style focused on obtaining absolute control of
        your body and dealing maximum damage to your opponent. The style focuses on using shockwaves-enhanced
        strikes to either obliterate your enemies completely or at the very least, wound them heavily.</i>
</p>

<h1 id="ability-title" class="text-left ml-5">Total Focus: Destructive Stance</h1>
<p id="ability-text" class="text-left mx-5 mb-2">Starting at 3rd level, as a bonus action, you can enter the
    Destructive Stance. When you first enter this stance, choose 1 creature to be your Total Focus opponent, for
    as long as you are in combat with your Total Focus target, you have advantage on checks to learn of its
    current location on the battlefield.</p>
<p id="ability-text" class="text-left mx-5 mb-2">In addition, choose a style when you first enter this stance.
    Once in a style, you can only use the techniques available for that style. To switch style will require you
    to spend a bonus action. Some techniques requires a saving throw, for which the DC will be 8 + your
    proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier.</p>

<b id="ability-text" class="text-left mx-5 mb-2">Styles:</b>

<ul class="text-left mx-5 mb-5">
    <li>
        <b id="ability-text" class="text-left mb-2">Fist Style</b>
        <ul class="text-left">
            <li>
                <p id="ability-text" class="text-left mb-2"><b>Air Type</b>: as an action, you can spend 2 Ki points to
                    send volleys of air shockwaves towards an enemy up to 30 ft away from you. The target must make a
                    Strength saving throw. On a failed save, it takes 3d10 Force damage and is knocked back up to 15 ft.
                    On a successful save, the creature takes half the damage and is not pushed back.</p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <p id="ability-text" class="text-left mb-2"><b>Discord</b>: when you land an unarmed strike, you can
                    spend 2 Ki points to empower your fists with compressed air. Until the end of your turn, all of your
                    unarmed strikes have a reach of 10 ft and does an extra 1d8 Force damage. The enhanced punches also
                    do Force damage instead of Bludgeoning damage for the duration.</p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <p id="ability-text" class="text-left mb-2"><b>Eight-Layered Crushing Core</b>: when you successfully
                    strike a creature and it is the 8th strike in total you have landed on that target, you can spend 2
                    Ki points to empower the strike. The target must make a Strength saving throw. On a failed save, it
                    takes 3d10 Force damage and has disadvantage on its first attack roll for 1d4 rounds. On a
                    successful save, the creature only suffers half the damage.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        <b id="ability-text">Leg Style</b>
        <ul class="text-left">
            <li>
                <p id="ability-text" class="text-left mb-2"><b>Crescent Split</b>: as a reaction to an incoming melee
                    attack, you can spend 1 Ki points to perform a vertical split kick and reduce the incoming damage by
                    1 roll of your Martial Arts die + your Dexterity modifier. If the damage is reduced to 0, you can
                    spend 1 Ki point to immediately make an Unarmed Strike as a triggered action.</p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <p id="ability-text" class="text-left mb-2"><b>Explosive Thousand Fury</b>: as an action, you can spend
                    2 Ki points to unleash a series of shockwaves kick in a 15ft cone. Creatures caught in the cone must
                    make Strength saving throws. On a failed save, a creature takes 4d6 Force damage and is knocked back
                    10ft. On a successful save, the creature only takes half the damage and is not pushed back.</p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <p id="ability-text" class="text-left mb-2"><b>Cascading Riverfall</b>: when making an Unarmed Strike,
                    you can spend 1 Ki point to increase the reach for that attack by 5 ft. If the attack hits, the
                    target takes an extra 1d8 Force damage and must succeed on a Strength saving throw or be knocked
                    Prone.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<hr class="mx-5 mb-5">

<h1 id="ability-title" class="text-left ml-5">Eradication Style</h1>
<p id="ability-text" class="text-left mx-5 mb-2">At 6th level, you learn an extra style in the Destructive Stance, the
    Eradication Style: as an action, you can spend 3 Ki points to enter a stance. You then leap 15 ft into the air and
    unleash a power punch towards a creature within 15 ft of you. The shockwave pressure emitting from your punch pushes
    down on the creature and it must make a Strength saving throw. On a failed save, it takes 5d10 Force damage and is
    Incapacitated till the end of its next turn. On a successful save, it takes half the damage and is not
    Incapacitated.</p>

<p id="ability-text" class="text-left mx-5 mb-5">In addition, the impact from the shockwaves shatters the ground
    beneath where the creature stands, creating a 15 ft radius crater and making the area difficult terrain. Creatures
    caught within the radius that is not the initial target of the attack must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or
    take 2d10 Force damage and half as much on a successful save.</p>

<hr class="mx-5 mb-5">

<h1 id="ability-title" class="text-left ml-5">Annihilation Style</h1>
<p id="ability-text" class="text-left mx-5 mb-5">At 11th level, you learn an extra style in the Destructive Stance, the
    Annihilation Style: as an action, you can spend 4 Ki points to lunge forward and perform a double punch towards a
    creature up to 30 ft from you. That target is pushed back 15 ft and must make a Strength saving throw or take 7d10
    Force damage. On a successful save, it takes half the damage. If the target is pushed into a wall, an obstacle or
    another creature, it takes additional Bludgeoning damage equal to your Wisdom modifier.</p>

<hr class="mx-5 mb-5">

<h1 id="ability-title" class="text-left ml-5">Final Destruction Style: Butterfly Flutter Afterglow</h1>
<p id="ability-text" class="text-left mx-5 mb-4">At 17th level, you learn the final technique in the Destructive Stance.
    As an action, you can spend 5 Ki points to target a creature up to 30 ft from you. You vanish into an afterimage,
    appearing next to your target in a 15 ft radius explosion of butterflies, forcing creatures caught in the radius to
    succeed on a Constitution saving throw or be blinded until the end of their next turn.</p>
<p id="ability-text" class="text-left mx-5 mb-5">You then perform an omni-directional barrage of shockwaves at the
    target. That creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or take 10d10 Force damage and at the start of
    each of its turn, it suffers 1 level of Exhaustion. On a successful save, it only takes half the damage.</p>